        <akn:num>50-921.35</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Rulemaking; enforcement.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_50-921_35_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Mayor, or his designee, may promulgate, amend, or repeal rules to implement the provisions of this subchapter, including the manner and amount of any fares, fees, or fines, pursuant to the Mayorâ€™s authority under subchapter I of Chapter 5 of Title 2.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_50-921_35_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Civil fines, penalties, and fees may be imposed as sanctions for an infraction of any rule promulgated under subsection (a) of this section pursuant to Chapter 18 of Title 2.</akn:p></akn:content>
